'''Botany''' is the [[Scientific method|scientific study]] of [[plant]][[life]]. As a branch of [[biology]], it is also sometimes referred to as '''plant science(s)''' or '''plant biology'''. Botany covers a wide range of scientific disciplines that study the [[Plant anatomy|structure]], [[cell growth|growth]], [[reproduction]], [[metabolism]], [[morphogenesis|development]] and [[phytopathology|diseases]] of [[plant]]s.  The study of plants and botany began with tribal lore, used to identify edible, medicinal and poisonous plants, making botany one of the oldest sciences.  From this the scope of botany has increased to include the study of over 550,000 kinds or species of living organisms.
